Every GreenHopper related chart accessed via Issue Navigator search results > Views > Charts will pop the following error message:
{quote}
There are problems with the current configuration for this gadget. The errors below may have been caused by the deletion of entities required by the gadget or by changes to your permissions.

Invalid project
{quote}

Every other chart builds based on the current issues in the Issue Navigator search results.

{panel:title=Atlassian Status as of 12 March 2012| borderStyle=solid| borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#49BD5F| bgColor=#E7F4FA}
We understand that the use of labels for Epics is not adequate to model the relationships between items in an Agile backlog. 

We have worked with the JIRA team to implement performant issue links. We can now use this form of issue relationship instead of labels. 

At this stage, we have not integrated this specific functionality in GreenHopper, though it can be used. In the future we will use it to model Epics (and more generally the breakdown of higher level stories in to smaller ones) in the GreenHopper Rapid Board. 
{panel}
